@node "Intro"
@title "Guidelist v1.0 - Introduction."
@{b}@{u}INTRODUCTION: @{ub}@{uu}

This program is made to keep track of files - mainly archives like Lha, DMS etc.

Let's say you have a modem and a lot of downloaded files. You copy these files
to some floppydisks for storage. Now you want to create some kind of list over
the disks, so that you are able to find the files again.

And this is exactly what guidelist does for you... The final list will be interactive and in Amigaguide format. It will contain name, size, date and description. When you click on the name, the file is processed - Take a look at this @{"example" link example.guide/main}.

In short Guidelist features:

 * Interactive Amigaguide lists.
 * User defined categories.
 * Description using File_ID.diz
 * Description editor.
 * Recognices a load of files (etc. lha,lzx,dms)
 * Full graphic userinterface.

In the above mentioned way you can scan all your floppies, CD's, HD's, ZIP's or what ever you like. In the end you will have a quick, functional & good looking filelist that will give you the desired file with a single mouseclick!

Enjoy the program.
@endnode
;--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

@node "Usage"
@title "Guidelist v1.0 - Usage."
@{b}@{u}USAGE: @{ub}@{uu}

View of the Guidelist window:

  @{"  Scan  " link "Usage"} @{"  Skib  " link "Usage"} @{"Edit ID " link "Usage"} @{"  Help  " link "Usage"}     Category ?

  Filename:                                  @{"Disk " link "Configfile"} @{"Docs " link "Configfile"}
  Size:                                      @{" Fun " link "Configfile"} @{"     " link "Configfile"}
  Date:                                      @{"     " link "Configfile"} .....
  Comment:                                   ....

  Status:


@{b}@{u}SCAN:@{ub}@{uu}

When you click on this button you will get a filerequester. Here you must select the file(s) you wish to create a list of.
Etc. You want to make a list of all the archives on DF0:. Now insert the disk in your drive, choose SCAN and select the files (see @{"Restrictions" link "Restrictions"}).
Data on the first file will now be presented - Name, size, date, comment & File_id.diz.
Now YOU must select in which category the file belong to. This is done by clicking one of the category-buttons.
When this is done the next file comes up...

@{b}@{u}SKIB:@{ub}@{uu}

This funktion skibs the current file - nothing is added to the list.

@{b}@{u}EDITID:@{ub}@{uu}

When clicked a small texteditor is popped up (Standart ED from AmigaOS). Here you may modify the description.
NOTE: Nothing is changed in the file - Only in the list.

@{b}@{u}HELP:@{ub}@{uu}

Gives you this guide.
@endnode
;--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node "Configfile"
@title "Guidelist v1.0 - The config file."
@{b}@{u}CONFIGURATION: @{ub}@{uu}

Guidelist's preferences can be altered in the file "GL:Guidelist.Config". In order to do this you must load the file into a text-editor. It is of great importance that the files are in the original order AND lines must NOT be deleted.

@{i}You need changing NOTHING in this file to make guidelist work - All paths & files are standart AmigaOS 3.0
@{ui}


@{b}GUIDE PATH: @{ub}

In the first line you must state where all the Guide-databases should be created.

1> GUIDEDIR GL:Guides/

Remember to end the paths with "/" and devices with ":".


@{b}CATEGORIES: @{ub}

In the 2nd to 11th line the Categories are set. 
You will find 2 colums - One with the button name & one with a filename (not path).

      <but>   <file>

  2>  Disk    Disk&Packers.Guide
  3>  Fun     Demo&Games.Guide
  4>  Emul    Emulat.....
  .
  .
  11> ..

Typing "Disk" in the first colum (<but>), gives you a @{"Disk" link ""}-button in the Guidelist window. Each time you click this button, the current file-description will be added to the filename "Disk&Packers.Guide" which are placed in the directory stated by GUIDEDIR in the 1st line.

IMPORTANT: * <but>  must have a length of max. 5 chars.
           * <file> Must NOT contain spaces!
           * You can max. have 10 buttons.
           * <but> and <file> must be separated by at least one space (NOT taps).
           * see also @{"Restrictions" link "Restrictions"}.


@{b}ARCHIVE BIT HANDLING: @{ub}

Guidelist has a mode that can prevent you from processing the same file twice: When a file has been added to a list the 'A'-flag is set. When Guidelist tries to proces a file with an 'A'-flag, the file is skibbed.
This function requires that the processed file is not write-protected - So forget it on CD's!
If you want to (de)activate this funktion, you may edit the 12'th line in the configfile:

  12> ARCBIT  OFF

Use ON or OFF.
@endnode
;--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

@node "install"
@title "Guidelist v1.0 - Installation."
@{b}@{u}INSTALLATION: @{ub}@{uu}

  To use Guidelist you will need the following:

    - Workbench 2.04+
    - ARexx
    - AmigaGuide or Multiview
    - C:Ed and all the (de)compressers (lha,lzx,unzip,,,)

  When you are ready - Just click on the installation icon.
@endnode

